<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-390-850  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 390 850.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>The LocalNetter  Oct 1990 v10 n10 p192(2)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Architecture Technology Corp. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>IBM AS/400 TCP/IP connectivity utilities enhanced.andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   International Business Machines Corp. (Marketing).andO;Ticker:    IBM.andO;Product:   IBM AS/400 (Minicomputer) (Computer programs).andO;Topic:     ConnectivityUtility ProgramsMarketing StrategyEnhancements.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>The Application System/400 (AS/400) support of Transmission ControlProtocol/Internet Protocol (TCP/IP) Connectivity Utilities is a licensedprogram that allows the customer to communicate with other systems anddevices that have implemented the TCP/IP suite of protocols.andP;  These utilitieshave been enhanced by IBM.andM;The AS/400 enhancements include TELNET, X.25 support, and IntegratedEthernet/IEEE 802.3 adapter support for TCP/IP.andP;  Along with these newfunctions are usability enhancements for configuration and management, andNational Language Support (NLS) compliance changes, the highlights of whichare further explained below:andM;The customer's investment in existing systems and devices is protected bypermitting the AS/400 system to function in an existing packet-switchednetwork or LAN, providing functions that capitalize on the equipment that iscurrently installedandM;Customer's growth is enhanced through connectivity support for TELNET clientand server, X.25 packet network, Ethernet 802.3 LAN with integrated adapters,and NLS support for TCP/IPandM;User productivity is enhanced by the addition of network status being addedto TCP/IP support, new configuration commands, and national languagetranslation of all messages and screens</TEXT></DOC>